Buildroot is a simple, efficient and easy-to-use tool to generate embedded
Linux systems through cross-compilation.

The documentation can be found in docs/manual. You can generate a text
document with 'make manual-text' and read output/docs/manual/manual.text.
Online documentation can be found at https://buildroot.org/docs.html

# RoboOS - Standard Robotics Operating System

![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-working-brightgreen)
![Architecture](https://img.shields.io/badge/architecture-ARM64-blue)
![Real-Time](https://img.shields.io/badge/real--time-PREEMPT__RT-red)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-GPL--2.0-green)

**RoboOS** is a hardware-agnostic, real-time operating system for robots, built with Buildroot, Linux, and PREEMPT-RT. It provides a single, reproducible build that runs on QEMU (for development) and on physical ARM64 hardware including Raspberry Pi 4, NVIDIA Jetson, and other platforms.

## ✨ Features

| Feature | Status | Description |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| **64-bit ARM64** | ✅ | Modern architecture for robotics |
| **PREEMPT-RT Real-Time** | ✅ | Deterministic kernel for motor control |
| **1000Hz Timer** | ✅ | Precise timing for control loops |
| **Hardware Agnostic** | ✅ | Same image runs on QEMU, RPi4, Jetson |
| **Custom Branding** | ✅ | ASCII art boot screen |
| **Reproducible Builds** | ✅ | Single `make` command |
| **QEMU Support** | ✅ | Test without hardware |
| **Network Stack** | ✅ | DHCP, TCP/IP ready |

## 🎯 Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Linux system (or GitHub Codespaces)
- Docker (optional) or native Linux environment
- Git

### Build RoboOS

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/deji4things2000/roboos.git
cd roboos

# Configure for QEMU (testing)
make roboos_final_defconfig

# Build the system (takes 1-2 hours)
make -j4

# Run in QEMU
./output/images/start-qemu.sh

#Login

Username: root
Password: (none - just press Enter)

#Enter Root Prompt

Type 'root' to enter into the OS root prompt

#Verify Real-Time

# Inside RoboOS
uname -a
# Should show: Linux RoboOS ... PREEMPT_RT ... aarch64

# Check kernel configuration
cat /proc/sys/kernel/printk

# Test latency (if cyclictest is installed)
cyclictest -t1 -p 80 -n -i 1000 -l 10000


#Building for aspberry Pi 4

# Configure for Raspberry Pi 4
make raspberrypi4_64_defconfig

# Enable real-time kernel
make linux-menuconfig
# General setup → Preemption Model → Fully Preemptible Kernel (Real-Time)

# Build
make -j4

# Flash to SD card
dd if=output/images/sdcard.img of=/dev/sdX bs=1M status=progress


